'''Al Amir Mohamed Waheed Deen''' ({{lang-dv|އައް ނަބީލް މުޙައްމަދު ވަހީދުއްދީން}}) is the current [[Vice President of the Maldives]]. He was appointed by President [[Mohamed Waheed Hassan]] on February 15, 2012, following the disputed resignation of the previous president, [[Mohamed Nasheed]]. He is also the Chairman of Bandos Island Resort. Deen is the son of Prince Abdullah Imaaduddeen and Koli Dhon Didi. He is also a member of the Maldivian Royal Family as his grandfather was Sultan [[Muhammad Imaaduddeen IV]].<ref>Haveeru News on 15th February 2012 , Maldives Royal Family Website </ref>
