{{Infobox officeholder |image =|thumb |office = [[Vice President of the Maldives]] |president = [[Mohammed Waheed Hassan Manik]] |term_start = 25 April 2012 |term_end = |predecessor = [[Mohammed Waheed Hassan Manik]] |successor = }}
'''Al Amir Mohammed Waheed Deen''' ({{lang-dv|އައް ނަބީލް މުޙައްމަދު ވަހީދުއްދީން}}) is the current [[Vice President of the Maldives]]. He was appointed by President [[Mohamed Waheed Hassan]] on February 15, 2012, following the disputed resignation of the previous president, [[Mohamed Nasheed]].<ref name=minivan>{{cite web|author=JJ Robinson and Hawwa Lubna |url=http://minivannews.com/politics/waheed-deen-nominated-as-vice-president-32174 |title=Waheed Deen nominated as Vice President |publisher=Minivan News |date=15 February 2012 |accessdate=9 November 2013}}</ref> He is also the Chairman of Bandos Island Resort.<ref name=minivan/> Deen is the son of Prince Abdullah Imaaduddeen and Koli Dhon Didi. He is also a member of the Maldivian Royal Family as his grandfather was Sultan [[Muhammad Imaaduddeen IV]].<ref>Haveeru News on 15th February 2012 , Maldives Royal Family Website </ref> He previously served as Atolls Minister until August 2008 under [[Maumoon Abdul Gayoom]].<ref name=minivan/><ref>{{cite web|author=Shantanu Guha Ray |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/maldives-india-ties-mohamed-waheed-mohammed-nasheed/1/188636.html |title=Maldives President Mohamed Waheed seeks predecessor Mohammed Nasheed's involvement to solve political crisis |publisher=India Today |date=14 May 2012 |accessdate=9 November 2013}}</ref>
