'''Al Amir Mohammed Waheed Deen''' ({{lang-dv|ވަހިއްދީންގެ އަމާ ދޮސް ފިނދު}}) served as the [[Vice President of the Maldives]] from April 25, 2012 to November 10, 2013. He was appointed by President [[Mohamed Waheed Hassan]] on February 15, 2012, following the disputed resignation of the previous president, [[Mohamed Nasheed]].<ref name=minivan>{{cite web|author=JJ Robinson and Hawwa Lubna |url=http://minivannews.com/politics/waheed-deen-nominated-as-vice-president-32174 |title=Waheed Deen nominated as Vice President |publisher=Minivan News |date=15 February 2012 |accessdate=9 November 2013}}</ref> He is also the Chairman of Bandos Island Resort.<ref name=minivan/> Deen is the son of Prince Abdullah Imaaduddeen and Koli Dhon Didi. He is also a member of the Maldivian Royal Family as his grandfather was Sultan [[Muhammad Imaaduddeen IV]].<ref>Haveeru News on 15th February 2012 , Maldives Royal Family Website </ref> He previously served as Minister of Atolls Development and Minister of Youth and Sports until August 2008 under [[Maumoon Abdul Gayoom]].<ref name=minivan/><ref>{{cite web|author=Shantanu Guha Ray |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/maldives-india-ties-mohamed-waheed-mohammed-nasheed/1/188636.html |title=Maldives President Mohamed Waheed seeks predecessor Mohammed Nasheed's involvement to solve political crisis |publisher=India Today |date=14 May 2012 |accessdate=9 November 2013}}</ref> He resigned from the Vice President’s post hours before the end of the presidential term, and after the country’s last ditch attempt to elect a new president before the constitutional deadline of November 11 failed after the Supreme Court suspended the runoff which was slated for 10 November. Neither the Vice President nor the Government stated the cause of the resignation.
